<p align="center"><h2><span id="title">Zonal statistics </span></h2><img id="icon" src="../icons/img_zonalstats.png" /></p>

<p><span id="section">Brief Description</span></p>

<p> Takes as input a raster layer containing a landscape and a raster layer with zones. Then it calculates general statistics for all values in the landscape raster layer which lie below a zone. For an explanation of the methodology see the help pages of <a href="http://help.arcgis.com/en/arcgisdesktop/10.0/help/index.html#/Zonal_Statistics/009z000000w7000000/">ArcGis SpatialAnalyst tool.</a></p>

<p><span id="section">Parameters</span></p>
<ul>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input landscape raster: </span>Classified raster to work on</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Input zone raster: </span>A raster layer containing zones</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Statistics: </span> The statistics to compute for each zone. Available are the mean, sum, minimum, maximum, standard deviation, variance, median and variety values.</p>
	</li>
	<li><p>
		<span>[param] Output table and/or raster: </span>Output to be generated. A table of the results is generated by default. If required a raster layer can be generated as well.</p>
	</li>	
</ul>

<p><span id="section">Limitations</span></p>
	<p><ul><li>The layers need to have the same projection, extent and resolution. Use the "Match Landscapes" and "Intersect Landscapes" tools beforehand if errors popup.</li></ul></p>
<p>
<span id="section">Info</span>
</p>

